youtube-dl is a '''command-line program''' to download videos from ''YouTube.com'' and other video sites. It is a free and open-source software written in ''Python''. The program provides an easy-to-use interface for downloading videos from various online platforms.

== Overview ==
youtube-dl is designed to be a simple and efficient way to download videos from the internet. It supports a wide range of video sites, including ''YouTube'', ''Vimeo'', and ''Dailymotion''. The program allows users to download videos in various formats, including ''MP4'', ''WebM'', and ''FLV''.

== Features ==
The key features of youtube-dl include:
* Downloading videos from ''YouTube'' and other video sites
* Supporting various video formats, including ''MP4'', ''WebM'', and ''FLV''
* Allowing users to select the video quality and format
* Providing an option to download subtitles and closed captions
* Supporting ''HTTPS'' and ''HTTP'' protocols

== Installation ==
To install youtube-dl, users can follow these steps:
* For ''UNIX'' users (''Linux'', ''macOS'', etc.), run the following command: <code>sudo curl -L https://yt-dl.org/downloads/latest/youtube-dl -o /usr/local/bin/youtube-dl</code> and <code>sudo chmod a+rx /usr/local/bin/youtube-dl</code>
* For ''Windows'' users, download the [youtube-dl.exe file](https://yt-dl.org/latest/youtube-dl.exe) and place it in any location on their ''PATH''
* Users can also install youtube-dl using ''pip'': <code>sudo -H pip install --upgrade youtube-dl</code>
* ''macOS'' users can install youtube-dl using [Homebrew](https://brew.sh/): <code>brew install youtube-dl</code> or [MacPorts](https://www.macports.org/): <code>sudo port install youtube-dl</code>

== Configuration ==
youtube-dl provides various options for configuration, including:
* Setting the output format and quality
* Selecting the video codec and container
* Enabling or disabling subtitles and closed captions
* Setting the proxy server and user agent

== Options ==
The program provides various options for customizing the download process, including:
* '''-f''', '''--format''' : Specify the video format
* '''-b''', '''--bitrate''' : Specify the bitrate
* '''-s''', '''--subtitle''' : Download subtitles
* '''-c''', '''--closed-captions''' : Download closed captions

== Output Template ==
youtube-dl allows users to specify a custom output template using the '''-o''' option. The template can include various placeholders, such as '''%(title)s''', '''%(id)s''', and '''%(format)s'''.

== Format Selection ==
The program provides an option to select the video format using the '''-f''' option. Users can specify the format code, such as '''136''' for ''MP4'' or '''244''' for ''WebM''.

== Video Selection ==
youtube-dl allows users to select a specific video quality using the '''-b''' option. Users can specify the bitrate, such as '''500k''' for ''500 kbps''.

